LISPKIT RELEASE CURRENT-VERSION
=====================

# OVERVIEW

LispKit is a framework for building Lisp-based extension and scripting
languages for macOS and iOS applications. LispKit is fully written in
the programming language Swift 5. LispKit implements a core language
based on the R7RS (small) Scheme standard. It is extensible, allowing
the inclusion of new native libraries written in Swift, of new libraries
written in Scheme, as well as custom modifications of the core
environment consisting of a compiler, a virtual machine as well as
the core libraries.

# INSTALL

Place the directory of this distribution anywhere and include the bin
directory of this distribution in your path.

# USAGE

lispkit [<option> ...] [---] [<program> <arg> ...]

options:
  -f, --filepath <value> ...
      Adds file paths in which programs are searched for.
  -l, --libpath <value> ...
      Adds file paths in which libraries are searched for.
  -a, --assetpath <value> ...
      Adds file paths in which assets are searched for.
  -d, --documents <value>
      Search for files and libraries in folder ~/Documents/<value>.
  -r, --root <value> ...
      Directories in which to search for files and libraries.
  -m, --memsize <value>
      Initial capacity of the heap memory.
  -n, --maxstack <value>
      Maximum stack size
  -i, --import <value> ...
      Imports library automatically after startup.
  --r7rs
      Imports library (scheme base).
  --lispkit
      Imports library (lispkit base).
  -p, --prelude <value>
      Path to prelude file which gets executed after loading all
      provided libraries.
  -c, --prompt <value>
      String used as prompt in REPL.
  -b, --basic
      Use basic line reader only.
  -e, --extendednames
      Use extended procedure names.
  -s, --strict
      In strict mode, initialization warnings terminate the application.
  -q, --quiet
      In quiet mode, optional messages are not printed.
  -u, --unformat
      Disable formatting of results.
  -t, --tabwidth <value>
      Width of a tab character.
  -x, --runloop
      Enable runloop, i.e. support asynchronous APIs
  -y, --systemstack <value>
      Stack size (in KB) of interpreter thread (if --runloop is used)
  -h, --help
      Show description of usage and options of this tools.

